      <note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Asmonius, (Apthonius the communis opinio, but see Prisc. 
        gramm. 3,420,1-7 and GL 6,80,30-81,3; [3. 62-68]). Aelius Festus Asmonius, Latin grammarian of the 
        4th cent. AD; author of a lost grammar dedicated to Constantius II (Prisc. gramm. 2,516,15-16) and
        of a comprehensive metrics in 4 books, which was already mutilated at the start as early as late 
        antiquity and was combined with the beginning of the grammar of Marius Victorinus (but cf. GL 6,173,32);
        furthermore A. may be the author of supplements to Horatian metrics and of metrical definitions (174-184)....." 
        Schmidt, Peter L. (Constance), “Asmonius”, in: Brill’s New Pauly, Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and ,
        Helmuth Schneider. Consulted online on 20 September 2016</note>
